<subSubSection id="C32C6528FFE7470BFF7DFDBDFE22FC52" pageId="35" pageNumber="134" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFE7470BFF7DFDBDFE02FD69" blockId="35.[242,1474,613,1018]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134">DESCRIPTION. — A densely squamose, pale grey species, usually having some pink sheen. Antennae slightly passing hind margin of eyes. Elytra distinctive for lacking tubercles at top of declivity, having instead interstriae 3 and 5 raised to low ridges.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFE7470BFE9FFD15FE4AFCE6" blockId="35.[242,1474,613,1018]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134">Male: tergite 7 broadly rounded, rather subtruncate. Sternite 9 with slender, weakly curved apodeme, with small expansion at apex. Aedeagal body as long as or up to 1.10 x longer than apodemes, weakly curved, acutely pointed at apex, shallowly emarginate at base; flagellum about as long as aedeagal body, evenly thick, lacking a heavily pigmented base.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFE7470BFE9FFC8FFCB7FC7C" blockId="35.[242,1474,613,1018]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134">Female: sternite 8 with slender apodeme; blade narrowly rounded. Distal hemisternites gently tapering, apical margin below styli distinctly oblique in relation to axis, with a very shallow concave curvature in it. Spermathecal duct extension elongate, gently curving away from stem; duct long, moderately thick, coiled for good part of length; stem lacking gland extension, only slightly thickened at this point.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936A3FFE7470BFE9FFC3AFE22FC52" blockId="35.[242,1474,613,1018]" box="[272,488,994,1018]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134">
Length: 
<quantity id="4CCE9B46FFE7470BFEE7FC3AFE2EFC52" box="[360,484,994,1018]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="35" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="7.55" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="6.3">6.3-8.8 mm</quantity>
